This paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) category as it discusses the evolution of soft robots and their control systems. It also touches upon the topic of adversarial examples, which is a common concern in the field of AI (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the interplay between different modalities, which suggests a systems perspective and could be relevant to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) category. Additionally, the use of evolutionary algorithms and learning algorithms suggests a connection to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) category. Finally, the mention of synaptic weights and the development of material properties suggests a connection to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) category.
